Jeanette Chabalala, News24Police. (News24, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A truck driver was shot in the arm and face during a hijacking in Kempton Park on Tuesday, paramedics and police said. He was attacked on Atlas Road, while on his way to work, Captain Kay Makhubela said.The hijackers left him on the side of the road and fled with the truck. No arrests had yet been made.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said the man was airlifted to hospital in a critical condition. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.